                    {
                        "unit_id": 4007,
                        "title": "Leveraging Local LLM and Hybrid Models",
                        "slug": "leveraging-local-llm-and-hybrid-models",
                        "order": 50,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "dyS31S7IcNU",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "<h5>When adopting AI, one size doesn’t fit all—especially when it comes to handling sensitive information. For many businesses, data security and privacy are top priorities. That’s where locally built Large Language Models, or LLMs, come into play. </h5>\r\n\r\n<h5>What are local LLM models? Unlike cloud-based solutions like OpenAI’s GPT or Google’s Gemini, local LLMs are AI systems hosted on your premises or a private infrastructure you control. These models are designed to ensure your data stays within your environment, reducing the risks associated with external data storage. </h5>\r\n\r\n<h5>Why is this important? First, it’s about compliance. Many industries have strict regulations about where and how data is stored. Hosting an LLM locally helps you meet those requirements, whether it’s GDPR in Europe or other regional standards. </h5>\r\n\r\n<h5>Second, it’s about control. With local models, you decide how your data is used, ensuring it’s not being shared, analyzed, or stored by third parties. This is especially critical if you handle confidential customer information, financial records, or intellectual property. </h5>\r\n\r\n<h5>Getting started with a local LLM might sound complex, but it’s more accessible than you think. Many ready-to-use solutions allow you to deploy and customize models on your infrastructure without extensive technical expertise. </h5>\r\n\r\n<h5>The benefits are clear: enhanced data security, compliance with regulations, and full control over your AI system. By choosing a local solution, you’re not just adopting AI—you’re doing it responsibly and strategically. </h5>",
